Paul Pogba’s brother, Mathias, has claimed that his sibling wants to leave Manchester United, so he can play in the Champions League and compete for titles. Pogba has not featured for United since Boxing Day due to an ankle injury. The World Cup winner is widely expected to leave Old Trafford this summer. The 26-year-old returned to Manchester United from Juventus in 2016 and has been linked with a return to Turin. Pogba has also been seriously linked with Real Madrid and Mathias explains why he wants to move. “Everyone knows that Paul wants to leave Manchester United, he wants to play Champions League football and win titles. “We all know that won’t happen at United. We will see what happens this summer,” he told El Chiringuito TV.